  {
    "Property": {
      "label": "P28",
      "name": "AuthHeaderExcluded",
      "params": [
        "r",
        "v1",
        "v2"
      ],
      "body": "( requestNormalized r /\\ fieldNormalized v1 /\\ fieldNormalized v2 ) ==>\ncanonicalizeS { r | hdrs = [ if h.isAuth then { h | value = v1 } else h\n| h <- r.hdrs ] }\n==\ncanonicalizeS { r | hdrs = [ if h.isAuth then { h | value = v2 } else h\n| h <- r.hdrs ] }",
      "doc": [
        "Two requests that differ ONLY in the bytes of their auth header value",
        "must produce the same canonical bytes — otherwise the signature would",
        "depend on itself.",
        "EXPECTED VERDICT: PASS. The encoder's `isAuth` skip enforces this; if a",
        "future refactor removes the skip, this property breaks immediately."
      ],
